Vol / Page: 87
Edition:
Quote: Having received them from a friend in Bermuda, Hugh planted two Avocado pear or subaltern's butter stones, but they had suffered in the voyage and did not even germinate, which we regretted, as they are a delicious fruit, and were unknown in New Zealand.
Notes: Quoted from 1908
